  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The scope of evaluation has further extended into specialized domains, with an increased emphasis on real-world scenario performance, as researchers develop dedicated benchmarks for embodied intelligence (Wang et al., 2024a; Yang et al., 2023; Zhang et al., 2023), medical image analysis (Xia et al., 2024; Chen et al., 2024a; Hu et al., 2024), chart understanding (Huang et al., 2025), and robotic control (Chen et al., 2024b; Wang et al., 2023c).",
    "In parallel with capability assessment, researchers have begun investigating LVLM robustness from two critical perspectives: first, examining semantic biases in model responses, particularly those related to societal factors like gender and racial prejudices (Wang et al., 2024c; Howard et al., 2024; Steed and Caliskan, 2021; Wu et al., 2024a); and second, analyzing adversarial vulnerabilities via carefully crafted visual prompts for assessing model reliability under targeted attacks (Liu et al., 2024a; Luo et al., 2024b; Zhang et al., 2024a; Wang et al., 2024c; Chen et al., 2023b).",
    "Yet, the capacity to withstand basic visual variations, a fundamental aspect of robustness widely present in real-world deployment, remains unexplored in current research.",
    "In this section, we propose a novel framework for automatically automatically generating diverse visual variations across task settings (3.1), along with a detailed description of the construction and char-acteristics of our evaluation dataset (3.2) and our evaluation protocols (3.3), as illustrated in Figure 1.",
    "The automated data generation pipeline incorporates four fundamental visual variations that are prevalent in real-world scenarios."
  ],
